article.headline: N. Iowa 76, Bradley 65
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Grant Stout scored 17 points and Eric Coleman added 16 as Northern Iowa beat Bradley 76-65 Wednesday night. Northern Iowa (10-2, 1-0 Missouri Valley Conference) came out with confidence early, shooting 56.7 percent in the first half and building an 18-point lead with 1:10 left before halftime. Bradley (9-4, 0-1) never led, but came within four points with about six minutes left in the game on a 3-pointer from Will Franklin. Stout scored seven of the Panthers' last nine points in the final minute to secure the win. Bradley shot 36.5 percent from the floor and was dominated inside by Stout and Coleman, who had 15 and 14 rebounds, respectively. In all, Bradley was outrebounded 45-28 and was outscored in the paint 32-12. Daniel Ruffin led Bradley with 20 points, Jeremy Crouch scored 14 and Franklin added 12. Northern Iowa led 42-28 at halftime.
